txt.en: You defeated a number of Easterlings and satisfied the bounty.
Easterlings can be found in Parth Daenath.\n\nYou should defeat Easterling beast-masters.
You satisfied the bounty on Easterlings in Parth Daenath. The frustrated soldier who posted it will be pleased that you went on the offensive.
Defeat Easterling beast-masters in Parth Daenath ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
A bounty notice asks you to take an offensive stance and defeat Easterling soldiers in Parth Daenath.

The bounty notice reads:

'How much of our time is spent making plans, or hiding behind crumbling fortifications? Too much, if you ask me! What we need to do is take the fight to the enemy. It is time to attack! If you share my convictions, you will pick up sword or axe and take action!

'Easterling soldiers have caused us no end of trouble during these years of siege. Attack them directly and you will achieve these two purposes: you will show them our strength, and you will earn yourself a good amount of coin!'
